The Hawks says one of the suspects is an immigration officer who is accused of fraudulently renewing passports in exchange for bribes. JOHANNESBURG Two men arrested for corruption at the South Africa and Namibia border will be appearing at the Springbok magistrates court in the Northern Cape on Wednesday.They have been charged with corruption and in contravention of the Immigration Act.The Hawks says one of the suspects is an immigration officer who is accused of fraudulently renewing passports in exchange for bribes.The second is a Zimbabwean national who was arrested for paying a bribe to have his documentation extended.The Hawks Philani Nkwalase says: &quot;What has been happening is that the foreign national would bring their own documentation, the passport and some of them were expired. And then they were fraudulently extended. So that has been the modus operandi.&quot;